				\begin{document}$$\mathrm{IPCE}(\% ) = \frac{{1240 \times J_{\mathrm{ph}}(\mathrm{mA}/\mathrm{cm}^2)}}{{\lambda (\mathrm{nm}) \times P_{\mathrm{light}}(\mathrm{mW}/\mathrm{cm}^2)}} \times 100\%$$\end{document}in which λ is the wavelength of the illuminating monochromatic photons, and Plight is the illuminating light power density at a given wavelength.

